# Project structure 

when starting a new session you should analyze the project using the repomix tool.  

The whole project is written in go.

## Modules
- ./sphinx - is a module used for encryption and decryption of blobs of data for onion routed encryption. 
- ./cmd/nostr-client/  - is an application to run a nostr client. 
- ./cmd/shallot/ - is an application to run a nostr relay using the kathru library that supports onion routing.
- ./circuit - is the internal library that handles routing for the onion relay and mantaining connections and sessions for routing. 


# Development practices
- use if statements with panics inside for testing things that should never happen in functions. 
- check for broken tests when finishing a task
- always use the standard testing go library.
- never commit any code changes.



